            <h3 style="margin:4px 0;">Common Questions</h3>
            <p><strong>Q:</strong> Can my dog wear the prong collar all the time?<br><strong>A:</strong> No — only during training or supervised walks. Remove it for play, rest, or unsupervised times.</p>
            <p><strong>Q:</strong> Is a prong collar painful?<br><strong>A:</strong> When used correctly it provides short, even pressure; it should not cause pain. Proper fit and technique are crucial.</p>
            <p><strong>Q:</strong> Who should I call for training help?<br><strong>A:</strong> We recommend consulting a positive-reinforcement certified trainer or a vet behaviorist for guidance.</p>
